,'Winner of the Grand Jury Prize at this year\'s Cannes Film Festival and a Golden Globe nominee for Best Foreign Language Film, the deeply moving new film by the Dardenne brothers delves into the emotional life of troubled 11-year-old Cyril (Thomas Doret). When his father (Jeremie Renier) abandons him, Cyril obsessively searches for his bicycle - placing his last bit of hope in this symbol of their relationship. Almost by accident, he becomes the ward of a kind hairdresser (Cecile de France), who seems surprised to find herself so determined to help him. With his wild, unpredictable behavior and his disastrous search for father figures, Cyril risks losing her - though she refuses to give up without a fight. -- (C) IFC','Thanks to the Dardenne brothers\' typically fine direction, The Kid with a Bike is a heart-wrenching, thematically and spiritually rich drama.','http://content6.flixster.com/movie/11/16/36/11163600_mob.jpg'),(499,'Bull Durham',1988,'http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/bull_durham/','16517','0094812',1,NULL,'Kevin Costner at his funniest and most charismatic in Bull Durham, a film that\'s as wise about relationships as it is about minor league baseball.','http://content6.flixster.com/movie/11/15/66/11156624_mob.jpg'),(500,'Battlefield Earth',2000,'http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/battlefield_earth/','11361','0185183',1,NULL,'Ugly, campy, and poorly acted, Battlefield Earth is a stunningly misguided, aggressively bad sci-fi folly.','http://content6.flixster.com/movie/26/03/260312_mob.jpg'),(501,'In the Bedroom',2001,'http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/in_the_bedroom/','13633','0247425',1,NULL,'Expertly crafted and performed, In the Bedroom is a quietly wrenching portrayal of grief.','http://content7.flixster.com/movie/11/15/36/11153629_mob.jpg'),(502,'Bully',2001,'http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/bully/','17062','0242193',1,NULL,'With its lingering shots of naked teenage bodies, Bully feels more sordidly exploitative than realistic.','http://content6.flixster.