eing Earnest',2002,'http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/importance_of_being_earnest/','10173','0278500',1,NULL,'Oliver Parker\'s adaptation of Oscar Wilde\'s classic play is breezy entertainment, helped by an impressive cast, but it also suffers from some peculiar directorial choices that ultimately dampen the film\'s impact.','http://content7.flixster.com/movie/25/44/254413_mob.jpg'),(518,'The Black Cauldron',1985,'http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/black_cauldron/','10554','0088814',1,NULL,'Ambitious but flawed, The Black Cauldron is technically brilliant as usual, but lacks the compelling characters of other Disney animated classics.','http://content8.flixster.com/movie/25/63/256314_mob.jpg'),(519,'Beautiful Boy',2010,'http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/beautiful_boy/','771208626','1533013',1,'Bill (Michael Sheen) and Kate (Maria Bello) hopelessly try to find some hint of an explanation after finding out that their only son committed a mass shooting at his university before taking his own life. They struggle numbly through the funeral, the media onslaught, and the awkward pity from relatives and friends. Their already strained marriage is tested as they realize all they have left with each other is their shared grief and confusion-and the unfortunate legacy of their son. This life-altering event forces Bill and Kate to face their feelings of guilt, rage, blame, self-discovery -and ultimately hope- so that they can finally see each other and their chance for happiness again with clear eyes. -- (c) Anchor Bay',NULL,'http://content7.flixster.com/movie/11/15/70/11157069_mob.jpg'),(520,'Butter',2012,'http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/butter_2011/','771208980','1349451',1,'Butter follows an ambitious woman (Jennifer Garner) who is married to Iowa\'s reigning butter sculpting champ (Ty Burrell) but decides to enter the race on her own when he retires. She\'s the shoo-in until an adopted young black girl (Yara Shahidi) discovers she has an uncanny talent for butter-carving and becomes a late-breaking favorite. -- (C) Weinstein','Despite its talented cast and a few funny moments, Butter\'s satirical aims are largely undone by a lack of subtlety and air of smugness.','http://content7.flixster.com/movie/11/16/66/11166653_mob.jpg'),(521,'Blood Work',2002,'http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/blood_work/','14988','0309377',1,NULL,'Blood Work is a routine, but competently made thriller marred by lethargic pacing.','http://content7.flixster.com/movie/11/16/13/11161317_mob.jpg'),(522,'This Boy\'s Life',1993,'http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/this_boys_life/','13933','0108330',1,NULL,'A harrowing, moving drama about a young boy, his single mother, and his abusive stepfather, This Boy\'s Life benefits from its terrific cast, and features a breakout performance from a young Leonardo DiCaprio.','http://content7.flixster.com/movie/10/89/12/10891257_mob.jpg'),(523,'The Good, the Bad, and the Weird',2008,'http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/good_the_bad_and_the_weird/','770681339','0901487',1,NULL,'Whilst never taking itself too seriously, this riotous and rollicking Sergio Leone-inspired Korean Western is serious fun.','http://content9.flixster.com/movie/10/95/49/10954943_mob.jpg'),(524,'Very Bad Things',1998,'http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/very_bad_things/','16423','0124198',1,NULL,'Mean-spirited and empty.','http://content9.flixster.com/movie/55/04/79/5504799_mob.jpg'),(525,'A Better Life',2011,'http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/a_better_life/','771182967','1554091',1,'From the director of About a Boy comes A Better Life - a touching, poignant, multi-generational story about a father\'s love and the lengths a parent will go to give his child the opportunities he never had. -- (C) Summit',NULL,'http://content6.flixster.com/movie/11/15/57/11155720_mob.jpg'),(526,'Brown Sugar',2002,'http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/brown_sugar/','10880','0297037',1,NULL,'Though predictable and possibly too sweet, Brown Sugar is charming, well-acted, and smarter than typical rom-com fare.','http://content6.flixster.com/movie/10/91/32/10913272_mob.jpg'),(527,'Bunraku',2011,'http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/bunraku/','770785560','1181795',1,'A mysterious drifter (Josh Hartnett) and an ardent young Japanese warrior Yoshi (Gackt) both arrive in a town that has been terrorized by outrageous and virulent criminals. Each is obsessed with his separate mission, and guided by the wisdom of The Bartender (Woody Harrelson) at the Horseless Horseman Saloon, the two eventually join forces to bring down the corrupt and contemptuous reign of Nicola (Ron Perlman), the awesomely evil \"woodcutter\" and his lady Alexandra (Demi Moore), a femme fatale with a secret past. This classic tale is re-vitalized and re-imagined in an entirely fresh visual context, set in a unique world that mixes skewed reality with shadow-play fantasy, a place where even the landscape can betray you. -- (C) Picturesque Films','Bunraku admirably strives for visual panache, but the staging, acting, and effects are dismal with a complete lack of excitement.','http://content9.flixster.com/movie/11/15/93/11159303_mob.jpg'),(528,'Beyond a Reasonable Doubt',2009,'http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/1212946-beyond_a_reasonable_doubt/','770804905','1183251',1,NULL,'Hackneyed and over dramatic, this undercooked courtroom drama suffers from bad dialogue and a twist ending you\'ll see from a distance.','http://content9.flixster.com/movie/10/88/11/10881191_mob.jpg'),(529,'I Saw the Devil',2010,'http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/akmareul_boattda/','771209003','1588170',1,'I SAW THE DEVIL is a shockingly violent and stunningly accomplished tale of murder and revenge from Korean genre master KIM Jee-woon (The Good, The Bad, The Weird and A Tale of Two Sisters). Oldboy\'s CHOI Min-sik plays Kyung-chul, a dangerous psychopath who kills for pleasure. The embodiment of pure evil, he has committed horrifying and senselessly cruel serial murders on defenseless victims, successfully eluding capture by the police. On a freezing, snowy night, his latest victim is the beautiful Ju-yeon, daughter of a retired police chief and pregnant fiancee of elite special agent Soo-hyun (The Good, The Bad, The Weird\'s LEE Byung-hyun). Obsessed with revenge, Soo-hyun decides to track down the murderer, even if doing so means becoming a monster himself. And when he finds Kyung-chul, turning him in to the authorities is the last thing on his mind. The lines between good and evil fall away in this diabolically twisted game of cat and mouse. Pushing the concept of revenge to its most extreme limits, KIM Jee-woon brilliantly transcends the police procedural and serial killer genres in surprising and thrilling new ways. -- (C) Magnet',NULL,'http://content9.flixster.com/movie/11/15/51/11155175_mob.jpg'),(530,'Baby Geniuses',1999,'http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/baby_geniuses/','11638','0118665',1,NULL,'Flat direction and actors who look embarrassed to be onscreen make Baby Geniuses worse than the premise suggests.','http://content7.flixster.com/movie/10/09/74/10097481_mob.jpg'),(531,'Babe: Pig in the City',1998,'http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/babe_pig_in_the_city/','9994','0120595',1,NULL,'Not quite as good as the original and has some dark subject material that might not be appropriate for children.','http://content6.flixster.com/movie/10/88/34/10883432_mob.jpg'),(532,'Vampire in Brooklyn',1995,'http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/vampire_in_brooklyn/','14915','0114825',1,NULL,'Neither scary nor very funny, this misguided effort never lives up to its premise.','http://content7.flixster.com/movie/10/88/64/10886457_mob.jpg'),(533,'The Black Balloon',2008,'http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/black_balloon/','770685824','0865297',1,NULL,'A tender and witty portrayal of a family coping with autism, The Black Balloon is heartfelt without being schmaltzy or moralizing.','http://content8.flixster.com/movie/10/86/38/10863802_mob.jpg'),(534,'All the Boys Love Mandy Lane',2006,'http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/mandy-lane/',