 in his life and death struggle to find beauty in a seemingly vicious and loveless world. -- (C) Tribeca Film','Detachment\'s heart is in the right place, but overall it doesn\'t offer any solutions to its passionate ranting.','http://content6.flixster.com/movie/11/16/30/11163060_mob.jpg'),(1728,'Taxi to the Dark Side',2007,'http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/taxi_to_the_dark_side/','770674670','0854678',1,NULL,'Taxi to the Dark Side is an intelligent, powerful look into the dark corners of the War on Terror.','http://content6.flixster.com/movie/11/12/77/11127704_mob.jpg'),(1729,'Double Take',2001,'http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/1104038-double_take/','12025','0238948',1,NULL,'Despite a good performance by Orlando Jones, the movie is ruined by a ridiculous, messy plot and fails to generate laughs.','http://content8.flixster.com/movie/26/35/263518_mob.jpg'),(1730,'The Million Dollar Hotel',2000,'http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/million_dollar_hotel/','14348','0120753',1,NULL,'Critics say the weirdness of The Million Dollar Hotel is more grating and pretentious than interesting. Also, it takes too long to get to the conclusion.','http://content7.flixster.com/movie/65/00/650017_mob.jpg'),(1731,'The Other Son',2012,'http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/the_other_son/','771313869','2073016',1,'\"The Other Son\" is the moving and provocative tale of two young men -- one Israeli, the other Palestinian -- who discover they were accidentally switched at birth, and the complex repercussions facing them and their respective families. (c) Cohen Media',NULL,'http://content7.flixster.com/movie/11/16/65/11166521_mob.jpg'),(1732,'The Door in the Floor',2004,'http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/door_in_the_floor/','13078','0348593',1,NULL,'Though uneven in tone, this is one of the better adaptations of John Irving\'s novels, with Jeff Bridges giving one of his best performances.','http://content6.flixster.com/movie/26/80/268000_mob.jpg'),(1733,'Death Defying Acts',2007,'http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/death_defying_acts/','770677843','0472071',1,NULL,'Pretty but dull, with unconvincing turns from Zeta-Jones and Pearce. If you want a period magician movie, seek out The Prestige or The Illusionist instead.','http://content7.flixster.com/movie/10/41/06/10410653_mob.jpg'),(1734,'Avenue Montaigne (Fauteuils d\'orchestre) (Orchestra Seats)',2006,'http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/avenue_montaigne/','335718520','0444112',1,NULL,'A cute and bubbly French comedy that carries no deeper lessons or agendas than to have a little fun for 90 minutes.','http://content6.flixster.com/movie/47/95/51/4795512_mob.jpg'),(1735,'The Wave',2011,'http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/the_wave_2008/','770682063','1063669',1,'Germany today. During a project week, high school teacher Rainer Wenger (Jurgen Vogel) comes up with an experiment in order to explain to his students how totalitarian governments work. A role-playing game with tragic results begins. Within a few days, what began as harmless notions, like discipline and community, builds into a real movement: The Wave. By the third day, the students start ostracizing and threatening others. When the conflict finally erupts into violence at an intramural water polo game, the teacher decides to break off the experiment. But it\'s too late. The Wave is out of control... -- (C) IFC','Based on a true story, though relocated to Germany, this thought provoking film has an interesting premise, but suffers through a lack of believability.','http://content6.flixster.com/movie/11/15/77/11157704_mob.jpg'),(1736,'Dirty Love',2004,'http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/dirty_love/','7980','0327643',1,NULL,'The laugh-free Dirty Love is a comedy dead zone -- it\'s aggressively crude and shoddily constructed.','http://content9.flixster.com/movie/10/92/39/10923995_mob.jpg'),(1737,'L\'annee derniere a Marienbad (Last Year at Marienbad)',1961,'http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/lannee_derniere_a_marienbad_1961/','21746','0054632',1,NULL,'Elegantly enigmatic and dreamlike, this work of essential cinema features exquisite cinematography and an exploration of narrative still revisited by filmmakers today.','http://content8.flixster.com/movie/30/77/307794_mob.jpg'),(1738,'Dr. Jekyll and Mr. Hyde',1931,'http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/1006207-dr_jekyll_and_mr_hyde/','271476635','0022835',1,NULL,'A classic. The definitive version of the Robert Louis Stevenson novella from 1931, with innovative special effects, atmospheric cinematography and deranged overacting.','http://content9.flixster.com/movie/11/15/55/11155539_mob.jpg'),(1739,'Let it Rain (Parlez-moi de la pluie)',2008,'http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/let_it_rain/','770792635','1065332',1,NULL,'Low-key to a fault, Let It Rain blends subtle political commentary with smart, thoroughly French comedy.','http://content8.flixster.com/movie/11/13/32/11133222_mob.jpg'),(1740,'Delirious',2006,'http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/10007902-delirious/','11895','0412637',1,NULL,'A funny, energetic satire of the paparazzi life and the entertainment industry, Delirious is another winner for indie helmer Tom DiCillo.','http://content8.flixster.com/movie/51/24/50/5124506_mob.jpg'),(1741,'Deliver Us from Eva',2003,'http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/deliver_us_from_eva/','14773','0301181',1,NULL,'Though Union and LL Cool J are appealing romantic leads, Deliver Us From Eva is too predictable and contrived.','http://content7.flixster.com/movie/27/62/276225_mob.jpg'),(1742,'Dark Star',1974,'http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/dark_star/','9528','0069945',1,NULL,'A loopy 2001 satire, Dark Star may not be the most consistent sci-fi comedy, but its portrayal of human eccentricity is a welcome addition to the genre.','http://content9.flixster.com/movie/25/14/251415_mob.jpg'),(1743,'Like Dandelion Dust',2010,'http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/like-dandelion-dust/','770809264','0981042',1,'Academy Award winner Mira Sorvino and Barry Pepper star in My Date with Drew director Jon Gunn\'s heart-wrenching tale of a recently released ex-con who uses a legal loophole to locate his son, who was adopted by an upper-crust family shortly after his father was incarcerated. When Rip Porter (Pepper) went to prison, his wife, Wendy (Sorvino), couldn\'t handle the responsibilities of being a single parent. Wanting the best for her newborn son, Joey, she put the boy up for adoption. Adopted by Jack (Cole Hauser) and Molly Campbell (Kate Levering), Joey now enjoys an idyllic life with his new parents in a small town just outside of West Palm Beach, FL. Then, one day, Jack and Molly receive a troubling phone call from the social worker who assisted with the adoption: Rip has just been released from prison, and he\'s eager to start a new life with his wife Wendy and son Joey (Maxwell Perry Cotton). A judge has just issued a ruling stating that the Campbells have no choice but to return Joey to his biological parents -- but what if Jack and Molly were simply to disappear with Joey, like dandelion dust, never to be seen again? The film is adapted from the best-selling novel by Karen Kingsbury. ~ Jason Buchanan, Rovi',NULL,'http://content8.flixster.com/movie/11/16/49/11164966_mob.jpg'),(1744,'We Are The Night',2011,'http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/we_are_the_night/','771217942','1692504',1,'Dennis Gansel, responsible for the hit The Wave, explores night time in Berlin to find a sect of seductive lady vampires that hide out in the city\'s alternative clubs and enjoy the luxury and pleasures their attained immortality provides them. A stylized vision of female vampirism, closer to films like The Hunger or the TV series True Blood than to Twilight, We Are the Night differs from other films present this year in Sitges because it gives the myth an image of sensuality, charisma and attraction, playing especially on fascination for the night. A fascination that Gansel uses almost paroxysmally to exploit the German capital\'s nighttime atmospheres. -- (C) IFC Entertainment',NULL,'http://content8.flixster.com/movie/11/15/76/11157610_mob.jpg'),(1745,'L\' Ora di Religione (Il Sorriso di Mia Madre) (The Religion Hour) (My Mother\'s Smile)',2002,'http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/lora-di-religione-il-sorriso-di-mia-madre-the-religion-hour-my-mothers-smile/','467316539','0317965',1,NULL,'Castellitto\'s performance is the strong center of this surreal, fascinating film about a man\'s questioning of his religious beliefs and his relation to his mother.','http://content7.flixster.com/movie/10/92/32/10923201_mob.jpg'),(1746,'Village of the Damned',1960,'http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/1022823-village_of_the_damned/','541970','0054443',1,NULL,'Chilling performances and a restrained, eerie atmosphere make this British horror both an unnerving parable of its era and a timeless classic.','http://content7.flixster.com/movie/11/15/07/11150725_mob.jpg'),(1747,'Right at Your Door',2005,'http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/right_at_your_door/','321756349','0458367',1,NULL,'Though Right at Your Door dips into melodrama at the end, it\'s an otherwise tense, effective, and eerily plausible doomsday scenario.','http://content8.flixster.com/movie/10/92/21/10922134_mob.jpg'),(1748,'Sin noticias de Dios (Don\'t Tempt Me)',2001,'http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/dont_tempt_me/','14835','0284491',1,NULL,'More Hellish than it is Heavenly, Agustin Diaz Yanes\' black comedy about the Earthly duel between two angels doesn\'t have enough genuine laughs to support its far-fetched premise.','http://content8.flixster.com/movie/38/55/86/3855862_mob.jpg'),(1749,'Sex & Drugs & Rock & Roll',2010,'http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/sex-drugs-rock-roll-2009/','770810558','1393020',1,'Andy Serkis stars as volatile British new wave icon Ian Dury in this biopic from BAFTA-nominated director Mat Whitecross (The Road to Guantanamo). As a young boy, Dury nearly died after being stricken with polio. Though the ravaging disease would leave him permanently disabled, however, it would also instill him with the drive and perseverance to become one of the most influential musicians of his generation. Along with his band Ian Dury & the Blockheads, the unpredictable rocker would become a key figure in the new wave movement of the late \'70s. But through it all Dury\'s abrasive behavior never subsided, even during quiet moments with his delicate young son, Baxter (Bill Milner). Ray Winstone, Naomie Harris, and Olivia Williams co-star. ~ Jason Buchanan, Rovi',NULL,'http://content6.flixster.com/movie/11/16/86/11168668_mob.jpg'),(1750,'Life During Wartime',2009,'http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/1211512-life_during_wartime/','770681055','0808526',1,NULL,'With Life During Wartime, Todd Solondz delivers an unexpected semi-sequel to Happiness in typically uncompromising fashion.','http://content9.flixster.com/movie/11/14/87/11148763_mob.gif'),(1751,'30 Days Of Night: Dark Days',2010,'http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/30-days-of-night-dark-days/','770859118','1320304',1,'Nearly a year after the vampire siege of Barstow, Alaska, lone survivor Stella (Kiele Sanchez) discovers that she isn\'t alone when she\'s recruited to eradicate the vampire menace once and for all. Her waking hours filled mourning the death of her late husband and her dreams haunted by visions of the creatures that turned him into a monster, Stella becomes the subject of much ridicule when she makes it her mission to convince the public that vampires truly exist. But just as the embarrassment is becoming too much to handle, three strangers (Harold Perrineau, Diora Baird and Rhys Coiro) present Stella with an opportunity to seek revenge by killing Lilith (Mia Kirshner), the vampire queen behind the Barstow massacre. Armed to the teeth and ready to die fighting, the brave quartet descends into the sewers beneath Los Angeles and begins their search for the elusive Lilith. But should she manage to find them first, the vampires will once again gain the upper hand. ~ Jason Buchanan, Rovi',NULL,'http://content8.flixster.com/movie/11/15/19/11151942_mob.jpg'),(1752,'Dogtooth (Kynodontas)',2009,'http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/dogtooth/','770816906','1379182',1,NULL,'It\'ll be too disturbing -- and meandering -- for some, but Dogtooth is as disturbing and startlingly original as modern filmmaking gets.','http://content7.flixster.com/movie/10/90/24/10902473_mob.jpg'),(1753,'The Moth Diaries',2012,'http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/the_moth_diaries/','771252555','1407065',1,'Acclaimed director Mary Harron returns with the chilling story of Rebecca (Sarah Bolger), a young girl who, haunted by her father\'s suicide, enrolls in an elite boarding school for girls. Before long, Rebecca\'s friendship with the popular Lucy (Sarah Gadon) is shattered by the arrival of a dark and mysterious new student named Ernessa (Lily Cole). Rebecca, whose overtures of concern are rejected by Lucy, finds herself lost and confused. Rebecca starts to suspect that Ernessa is a vampire, but, despite the suspicious deaths that begin to occur, her fears are treated as simple girlish jealousy. As the bodies of young girls pile up and the line between reality and the supernatural starts to blur, Rebecca decides to take matters into her own hands and get rid of Ernessa. -- (C) IFC',NULL,'http://content9.flixster.com/movie/11/16/38/11163871_mob.jpg'),(1754,'Dead Man Running',2009,'http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/dead-man-running/','770808477','1311699',1,NULL,'Poor performances, stiff dialogue, flat characters, and an unimaginative stab at the mood of the Guy Ritchie crime caper make Dead Man Running into a hooligan tale with little to offer.','http://content7.flixster.com/movie/11/16/86/11168677_mob.jpg'),(1755,'Half Past Dead',2002,'http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/half_past_dead/','11439','0297162',1,NULL,'Seagal is now too bulky to make a convincing action hero, and Half Past Dead is too silly and incoherent to deliver any visceral kicks.','http://content9.flixster.com/movie/10/88/11/10881139_mob.jpg'),(1756,'Der Krieger und die Kaiserin (The Princess and the Warrior)',2000,'http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/princess_and_the_warrior/','13966','0112230',1,NULL,'More slow-moving than Run Lola Run, this film nonetheless offers an intriguing storyline about love and fate.','http://content8.flixster.com/movie/27/23/272322_mob.jpg'),(1757,'Eat Drink Man Woman (Yin shi nan nu)',1994,'http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/eat_drink_man_woman/','17093','0111797',1,NULL,'A richly layered look at the complex interactions between a widowed chef and his daughters, Ang Lee\'s generational comedy Eat Drink Man Woman offers filmgoers a tasty cinematic treat.','http://content8.flixster.com/movie/28/62/286218_mob.jpg'),(1758,'2 Days in the Valley',1996,'http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/2_days_in_the_valley/','13366','0115438',1,NULL,'A labyrinthine thriller with a host of memorable characters, 2 Days in the Valley is an uneven but intriguing thriller/black comedy.','http://content6.flixster.com/movie/26/94/269408_mob.jpg'),(1759,'Samson and Delilah',2009,'http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/10011295-samson_and_delilah/','770808521','1340123',1,NULL,'Alternately beautiful and heartrending, Samson and Delilah is terrifically acted and shot, and presents a complex portrait of what it means to be Australian.','http://content9.flixster.com/movie/10/87/63/10876371_mob.jpg'),(1760,'Il Divo',2008,'http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/il_divo/','770761058','1023490',1,NULL,'While the web of corruption in this Italian political thriller can be hard for a non-native to follow, the visuals and the intrigue are compelling and thrilling in equal measure.','http://content6.flixster.com/movie/10/84/85/10848504_mob.jpg'),(1761,'The Boss of it All (Direktoren for det hele)',2006,'http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/1174004-boss_of_it_all/','415813253','0469754',1,NULL,'Director Lars von Trier ditches the pretensions but keeps his misanthropy in The Boss of it All, a surprisingly sharp and witty comedy about office life gone haywire.','http://content7.flixster.com/movie/10/91/35/10913565_mob.jpg'),(1762,'Any Day Now',2012,'http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/any_day_now_2012/','771304313','2066176',1,'Inspired by a true story and touching on legal and social issues that are more relevant now than ever, ANY DAY NOW tells a story of love, acceptance, and creating your own family. In the late 1970s, when Marco (Isaac Leyva), a teenager with down syndrome who\'s been abandoned by his mother, is taken in by committed couple Rudy (Alan Cumming) and Paul (Garret Dillahunt), he finds in them the family he\'s never had. However, when their unconventional living arrangement is discovered by the authorities, Rudy and Paul must fight a biased legal system to adopt the child they have come to love as their own. (c) Music Box Films',NULL,'http://content8.flixster.com/movie/11/16/75/11167534_mob.jpg'),(1763,'In Dreams',1999,'http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/in_dreams/','16150','0120710',1,NULL,'Some interesting visuals, but the movie is as confusing as a dream.','http://content6.flixster.com/movie/10/95/41/10954128_mob.jpg'),(1764,'Elsker dig for evigt (Open Hearts)',2002,'http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/open_hearts/','559817072','0315543',1,NULL,'Pulsing with honesty, this film lays bare the rawness of human emotion with a story made all the more believable thanks to its gritty, low-budget approach.','http://content9.flixster.com/movie/50/91/95/5091955_mob.jpg'),(1765,'The Death of Mr. Lazarescu (Moartea domnului Lazarescu)',2005,'http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/1158218-death_of_mr_lazarescu/','326300130','0456149',1,NULL,'Shot in naturalistic style, this is a powerful indictment of absurdity and indifference in the face of human suffering.','http://content7.flixster.com/movie/27/36/69/2736693_mob.jpg'),(1766,'Delicacy',2012,'http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/delicacy/','771247386','1828995',1,'Audrey Tautou is Nathalie, a beautiful, happy, and successful Parisian business executive who finds herself suddenly widowed after a three-year marriage to her soul mate. To cope with her loss, she buries herself and her emotions in her work to the dismay of her friends, family and co-workers. One day, inexplicably, her zest for life and love is rekindled by a most unlikely source, her seemingly unexceptional, gauche, and average looking office subordinate, Markus (comic star Francois Damiens). At first stunned by Nathalie\'s unexpected attention, Markus comes to gradually believe in her feelings and shifts into romantic high gear. As their relationship goes from awkward to genuinely loving, Nathalie and Markus will have to overcome a host of obstacles including everyone else\'s judgmental perceptions as well as their own self-doubts. -- (C) CMG',NULL,'http://content9.flixster.com/movie/11/16/35/11163579_mob.jpg'),(1767,'Roger Dodger',2002,'http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/roger_dodger/','16578','0299117',1,NULL,'The movie could have benefited from a more experienced director, but a great cast and script overcome any first time jitters the director may have had.','http://content9.flixster.com/movie/12/88/67/1288679_mob.jpg'),(1768,'David & Layla',2008,'http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/david_and_layla/','395112450','0424025',1,NULL,'Earnest and well-intentioned, \"David & Layla\" stumbles over itself too often to achieve its goals.','http://content8.flixster.com/movie/34/21/51/3421510_mob.jpg'),(1769,'La Vie Revee des Anges (The Dreamlife of Angels)(The Daydreams of Angels)',1998,'http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/dreamlife_of_angels/','15518','0120449',1,NULL,'Showcasing excellent lead performances, The Dreamlife of Angels is an intelligent, absorbing character study of two women.','http://content8.flixster.com/movie/10/89/39/10893934_mob.jpg'),(1770,'The Duellists',1977,'http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/duellists/','11036','0075968',1,NULL,'Rich, stylized visuals work with effective performances in Ridley Scott\'s take on Joseph Conrad\'s Napoleonic story, resulting in an impressive feature film debut for the director.','http://content7.flixster.com/movie/11/12/21/11122181_mob.jpg'),(1771,'Dragon',2012,'http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/swordsmen/','771242451','1718199',1,'Liu Jin-xi (Yen) is a village craftsman whose quiet life is irrevocably shattered by the arrival of two notorious gangsters in the local general store. When Liu single-handedly saves the shopkeeper\'s life, he comes under investigation by detective Xu Bai-jiu (Kaneshiro). Convinced that Liu\'s martial arts mastery belies a hidden history of training by one of the region\'s vicious clans, Xu doggedly pursues the shy hero-and draws the attention of China\'s criminal underworld in the process (c) Weinstein Co.',NULL,'http://content9.flixster.com/movie/11/16/73/11167303_mob.jpg'),(1772,'Dummy',2003,'http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/1125540-dummy/','14045','0246592',1,NULL,'Just zany enough to be entertaining without succumbing heavily to tired oddball antics, Dummy is a sweet family comedy that succeeds due to charming performances, even if the final product feels slightly undercooked.','http://content9.flixster.com/movie/27/27/272719_mob.jpg'),(1773,'Hara-Kiri: Death of a Samurai',2012,'http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/hara_kiri_death_of_a_samurai/','771241155','1728196',1,'From visionary auteur Takashi Miike comes the story of a mysterious samurai who arrives at the doorstep of his feudal lord, requesting an honorable death by ritual suicide in his courtyard. The lord threatens him with the brutal tale of Motome, a desperate young ronin who made a similar request with ulterior motives, only to meet a grisly end. Undaunted, the samurai begins to tell a story of his own, with an ending no one could see coming. With stunning cinematography and gripping performances, Hara-Kiri: Death of a Samurai is a thrilling exploration of revenge, honor, and individuality in the face of oppressive power. -- (C) Tribeca Film',NULL,'http://content8.flixster.com/movie/11/16/56/11165698_mob.jpg'),(1774,'Moby Dick',1956,'http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/1014090-moby_dick/','18370','0049513',1,NULL,'It may favor spectacle in place of the deeper themes in Herman Melville\'s novel, but John Huston\'s Moby Dick still makes for a grand movie adventure.','http://content6.flixster.com/movie/11/15/67/11156744_mob.jpg'),(1775,'Latter Days',2003,'http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/latter_days/','16975','0345551',1,NULL,'A melodramatic plot and character stereotypes turn the movie into a sitcom.','http://content7.flixster.com/movie/28/56/285629_mob.jpg'),(1776,'Quill: The Life of a Guide Dog',2012,'http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/quill_the_life_of_a_guide_dog/','603201623','0400761',1,'Based on a true story, Quill: The Life of a Guide Dog is the sweet tale of a yellow Labrador Retriever guide dog for the blind named Quill. We follow Quill from the litter to his selection as a guide dog shortly after his first birthday. After training at a school for guide dogs, Quill is paired with a blind man named Watanabe who at first is reluctant to rely on him. But Quill\'s great patience, gentleness and skill eventually win him over and they become inseparable friends. -- (C) Music Box Films',NULL,'http://content8.flixster.com/movie/11/16/44/11164430_mob.jpg'),(1777,'Death Race 2',2010,'http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/death_race_2/','771197786','1500491',1,'Luke Goss, Ving Rhames, Sean Bean, and Danny Trejo headline director Roel Reine\'s thrill-ride sequel to Paul W.S. Anderson\'s hyper-violent remake exploring the origins of the most notorious Death Race competitor ever to take the wheel. Featuring a screenplay by Tony Giglio (Chaos), Death Race 2 follows convicted cop-killer Carl Lucas (Goss) as he vies for freedom by competing in the most deadly reality show ever conceived. The U.S. economy has completely collapsed, and as lawlessness spreads, private prisons crop up all across the country. Corruption reigns in these for-profit penitentiaries, and Terminal Island is home to some of the most violent offenders in the world. Lucas has just been handed a life sentence for killing a cop. Just when it looks like he\'ll be spending the rest of his days behind bars, unscrupulous television producer September Jones shows up seeking contestants for a brutal new game show where prisoners battle it out in high-performance death machines equipped with lethal weapons. The reward for surviving this psychotic demolition derby: freedom. Before long Lucas is fastening his seat belt, and preparing for the ride of his life. By the time this race is over, an apocalyptic legend will be born. ~ Jason Buchanan, Rovi',NULL,'http://content7.flixster.com/movie/11/16/82/11168285_mob.jpg'),(1778,'What\'s Up, Doc?',1972,'http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/whats_up_doc/','9425','0069495',1,NULL,'Barbra Streisand was never more likable than in this energetic, often hilarious screwball farce from director Peter Bogdanovich.','http://content9.flixster.com/movie/10/91/86/10918647_mob.jpg'),(1779,'Day Night Day Night',2006,'http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/day_night_day_night/','688972597','0499455',1,NULL,'Day Night Day Night is a minimalist drama that refuses to indulge in stereotypes, making it all the more realistic and chilling.','http://content9.flixster.com/movie/75/69/37/7569379_mob.jpg'),(1780,'Doghouse',2009,'http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/doghouse/','770809868','1023500',1,NULL,'An amateurish, unfunny and unscary British horror-comedy that could be accused of misogyny.','http://content9.flixster.com/movie/11/16/86/11168679_mob.jpg'),(1781,'Lights in the Dusk (Laitakaupungin valot)',2006,'http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/lights_in_the_dusk/','410617659','0458242',1,NULL,'From its brilliant cinematography to its compassionate characters, Lights in the Dusk is another successful exercise in deadpan minimalist comedy from Aki Kaurismaki.','http://content9.flixster.com/movie/35/54/03/3554035_mob.jpg'),(1782,'The Details',2012,'http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/the_details_2010/','771225039','1433207',1,'After ten years of marriage, Jeff and Nealy Lang (Tobey Maguire and Elizabeth Banks) have an idyllic suburban home... and a relationship on the skids. But, when a family of hungry raccoons ransacks their perfectly manicured backyard, Jeff becomes single-mindedly obsessed with eradicating the pests by any means necessary. Soon the relentless rodents aren\'t merely uprooting the lawn, but also overturning the Langs\' entire bourgeois existence, as the man-versus-beast battle leads into an absurd mess of infidelity, extortion, organ donation and other assorted mayhem. -- (C) Radius TWC',NULL,'http://content6.flixster.com/movie/11/16/71/11167100_mob.jpg'),(1783,'Dr. T & The Women',2000,'http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/dr_t_and_the_women/','15142','0205271',1,NULL,'In terms of quality, Dr. T and the Women is one of Altman\'s good-but-not-great films. In typical Altman style, it features some great ensemble acting, including a wonderful performance by Richard Gere.','http://content9.flixster.com/movie/10/88/12/10881219_mob.jpg'),(1784,'Kiss of Death',1995,'http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/1060720-kiss_of_death/','15057','0113552',1,NULL,'An outstanding ensemble cast propels Kiss of Death, a noir-ish crime thriller that\'s slick and big on atmosphere, even if its script may only provide sporadic bursts of tension.','http://content6.flixster.com/movie/27/76/277616_mob.jpg'),(1785,'The Good Doctor',2012,'http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/the_good_doctor_2011/','771204404','1582271',1,'Martin Blake (Orlando Bloom) is an ambitious but anxious young doctor, eager to impress his superiors and colleagues: Chief Resident Waylans (Rob Morrow), self-assured fellow intern Dan (Troy Garity) and no-nonsense nurse Theresa (Taraji P. Henson). But things are not going Martin\'s way and he can\'t seem to shake off his insecurities. When 18-year-old patient Diane (Riley Keough) is admitted for a kidney infection, Martin steps in, getting the much-needed boost of self-esteem he craves. But things take a